  "prompt": "What happened in 2008 financial crisis?",
  "response": "The 2008 financial crisis was a severe global economic downturn triggered primarily by the collapse of the U.S. housing market and subprime mortgage crisis. Here are key details:\n\n1. Causes:\n- Widespread risky mortgage lending\n- Complex financial derivatives based on subprime mortgages\n- Housing market bubble\n- Lack of financial regulation\n- Banks offering loans to borrowers with poor credit\n\n2. Major Events:\n- Housing prices collapsed\n- Subprime mortgage defaults increased dramatically\n- Lehman Brothers bankruptcy\n- Stock market crash\n- Credit markets froze\n- Major financial institutions required government bailouts\n\n3. Consequences:\n- Global recession\n- Massive job losses\n- Significant decline in home values\n- Stock market plummeted\n- Millions of foreclosures\n- Government bailouts of banks and financial institutions\n- Long-term economic impact\n\n4. Key Financial Institutions Affected:\n- Lehman Brothers (collapsed)\n- AIG\n- Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac\n- Bear Stearns\n- Merrill Lynch\n\n5. Government Response:\n- Troubled Asset Relief Program (TARP)\n- Stimulus packages\n- Federal Reserve interventions\n- Stricter financial regulations (Dodd-Frank Act)\n\nThe crisis fundamentally reshaped global financial systems and economic policies.",
